,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Upcoming Gala Event','none',' Starkey Hearing Foundations annual So the World May Hear Awards Gala celebrates the spirit of giving.The gala showcases the tremendous impact of reflecting caring and sharing into the lives of others. With the support we receive at the Gala, we are able to use hearing as a vehicle to change lives and give more than 100,000 hearing aids annually to people in need. Each year we honor humanitarians who dedicate their time and service to helping others around the world and here at home, and we have amazing perfor- mances from world-class entertainers.','none','','xhtml',2014,'none','vikings_mission.jpg','none',' ','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(106,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'false','none','BLOG-Tani_Austins_Inspiring_Words-_Mexico-Colombia-_THUMBNAIL.png','none','News','none',1304751600,'','none','<p>Sunday April 17, 2011: It&#39;s been a very busy week for the Foundation in the media world (USA Today, \"The Celebrity Apprentice\" and Gary Busey on \"The Tonight Show with Jay Leno\" &amp; \"The Ellen DeGeneres Show\") PLUS being on the road! Once again our sponsors could not go with us so we asked a few employees to go along. Todd Hedberg, whom I had never met and Derek Johnson from Customer Service, both bilingual. Mucho mucho bueno! Big Big Help! Along with Fred, Rachael, Mark, Justin and Rene, Bill took off for Mexico with just two hours in between flights in Minneapolis.</p>\n\n<p>The team met up with more Starkey employees in Brownsville, Texas headed by Starkey Mexico manager, Dora Ayala and her team. Beautifully organized missions in partnership with the Lions Club chapter in Matamoras, Monterrey and San Luis Potisi. Thousands received the gift of hearing with many beautiful stories and tears of joy. No better story than the ending day in San Luis Potisi, when we were packing up to catch the plane to Colombia when Rene asked Bill if we could fit two young men that had walked up even though we were almost packed up. Bill never ever hesitates to say yes even though this will put time stress on us.</p>\n\n<p>Amazingly these young men were begging on the side of the road when this woman stopped to see what they needed (even though it is extremely dangerous time in Mexico and was absolutely NOT the thing to do). Turns out the two were deaf and the woman had heard about the Lions Club/SHF Better Hearing Mission on the radio. She told them to get in the car and drive to her friend&rsquo;s house whose husband is with the Lion&#39;s Club. Her friend called her husband at work to ask where the mission was being held, he told her where and they rushed right over to the mission site just barely catching us. Both young men had no speech, one takes two 70 gain aids and the other takes two 50 gain aids, neither one of them can believe this is happening. It was a leap of faith by all parties and the message that there is so much good left in the world!</p>\n\n<p>Onto Colombia, where the Starkey staff is waiting at the airport and we see the smiling face of Catalina Parra, manager of Starkey Colombia, as we walk out of customs. All throughout the airport the Colombian workers were thanking us for helping the children so we knew right away Catalina had spread the word (this rarely happens in customs!). The Colombian people are so very gracious and gave us many, many blessings and celebrations. We have been in Cali and Cartegna working with four of our customers along with Starkey Colombia Team.</p>\n\n<p>Always smiles and blessings! We work at the University tomorrow and finish up the run delivering over 5,000 hearing aids to some very deserving and gracious people. They say over and over \"God Bless you\" and we always say \"He does!\"</p>\n\n<p>Thank You to ALL the Starkey Team that makes this happen!</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_357:{filedir_2}BLOG-_Tani_Austins_inspiring_words-_Mexico_and_Colombia-_01.png}\" style=\"height:525px; width:767px\" /></p>','none','Tani Austin ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-Tani_Austins_inspiring_words-_Mexico-_Colombia_-LEAD.png','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(107,1,12,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,' ','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(108,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','Blog_Philippines_.jpg','none','News','none',1387488240,'','none','<p><strong>Caring for Our Friends in the Philippines</strong></p>\n\n<p>Over 35 days, four countries and 10 cities, the hearing mission team finished the year strong, fitting more than 12,000 people. Crisscrossing Asia, we brought the gift of hearing to India, Cambodia, China and completed our tour with an impactful, four-city hearing mission in the Philippines.</p>\n\n<p>Typhoon Haiyan struck the Philippines three weeks before our long-scheduled hearing mission was set to take place. For a second after that tragedy, we paused to consider how to help, and we decided that the best thing we could do was go, as planned, to give the gift of hearing. Joined by boxing champion Manny Pacquiao, fresh from his victory in China, and singer Jessica Sanchez, we brought our love and care to more than 5,000 people in need.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_366:{filedir_2}BLOG-December_newsletter_caring_for_our_friends_in_the_Philippines-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:697px\" /></p>\n\n<p>In his hometown of General Santos, Pacquiao proudly joined the hearing mission team to give back to his local community. He fulfilled two wishes for one young man who got to meet both his hero and receive the gift of hearing.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_367:{filedir_2}BLOG-December_newsletter_caring_for_our_friends_in_the_Philippines-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:774px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Excited to be as hands-on as possible with the patients, Sanchez worked and traveled with the team for the entire hearing mission. Her first day on the job she helped reconnect 88-year-old Maria Solis Sogon with her 12 children, 20 grandchildren and 5 great-grandchildren. Overwhelmed with gratitude, Maria broke into song to Sanchez&rsquo;s delight. By the end of the hearing mission, it was Sanchez who was moved to song by all of the incredible people and lives she was able to help change. She performed for a captivated audience, giving many of them their first experience of music.</p>\n\n<p>From General Santos to Lipa City to Batangas to Manila, the team was inspired by the resilience of the Philippines. While many may have been knocked down by the impact of Typhoon Haiyan, from what we experienced, their spirit has not been broken. It will not take long for the Philippines to be just as strong, if not stronger than it was before.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Happy Holidays!</strong></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_368:{filedir_2}BLOG-December_newsletter_caring_for_our_friends_in_the_Philippines-03.jpg}\" style=\"height:234px; width:300px\" /></p>\n\n<p>With the holidays upon us, the team is busy preparing for another year of changing lives, while also spending some quality time with the people we love. From the Starkey Hearing Foundation family to yours, we wish you all love, light and peace this holiday season. Thank you for all you do to support our efforts around the world. May 2014 bring you inspiration and adventure!</p>\n\n<p>As you spend time with your friends and families this holiday season, remember the connecting power of hearing.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://action.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/\">Pledge your support </a>today and help us give that same connection to thousands of families around the world in 2014.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-December_newsletter_caring_for_our_friends_in_the_Philippines-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(109,1,12,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,' ','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(110,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'false','none','BLOG-Powering_inspiration_in_eden_prairie-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Hearing Missions','none',1379710020,'','none','<p>Katie Timmer is a multi-talented fireball of energy who has been inspiring others with her athletic ability through Special Olympics for more than 30 years. Her aptitude for sports has led her to swimming, golf, bocce ball, track and field and bowling, and it has also garnered the attention of sports stars like Tiger Woods and Matt Blair. Her mother and coach Pat expressed great pride in her daughter saying, &ldquo;The minimum age for participating in the Special Olympics is eight, and Katie just counted down the days until her eighth birthday when she could become a part of this incredible organization.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>However, Katie&rsquo;s path to success has not been without some extraordinary challenges caused by hearing loss. Due to Katie&rsquo;s high pain tolerance, as a child she suffered many ear infections that went undetected. In addition, her love of swimming created issues with swimmer&rsquo;s ear and a recurring need for tubes in her ears. After several surgeries, Katie and her family had resigned themselves to the fact that her right ear could be treated with a hearing aid, but she would never hear out of her left ear again. Katie learned to adapt, but her mother always felt that if she could only have the use of both of her ears, she wouldn&rsquo;t have to struggle so much to excel.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_371:{filedir_2}BLOG-Powering_inspiration_in_eden_prairie-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:814px\" /></p>\n\n<p>At our recent Special Olympics mission in Eden Prairie, Minnesota, Bill Austin gave Katie the gift of hearing in BOTH of her ears. Shocked and overjoyed, Katie and her mother expressed their amazement and gratitude in a recent video. Check it out!</p>\n\n<p>[gallery id=\"blog-powering-inspiration-in-eden-prairie-film\"]</p>','none','Foundation Staff','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-Powering_inspiration_in_eden_prairie-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(112,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-November_Newsletter_Minnesota_Vikings_partner_for_homegrown_hearing_mission-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','News','none',1385072880,'','none','<p>Minnesota Vikings Partner for Homegrown Hearing Mission</p>\n\n<p>After an incredible six-city hearing mission in <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/africa/kenya-10-2013/\">Kenya</a>, the team returned home for a very special homegrown mission. Traveling from nearby Metro Deaf School and Faribault School for the Deaf, and from as far away as California, Missouri and Indiana, more than 50 patients arrived at our headquarters for a hearing mission with the <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/usa/us-minnesota-10-2013/\">Minnesota Vikings </a>and Starkey Hearing Technologies. Overjoyed to meet their heroes, the children taught Vikings stars Adrian Peterson, Greg Jennings, Josh Freeman, Jerome Simpson and Greg Childs some sign language, while the players doled out encouragement, inspiration and autographs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_374:{filedir_2}BLOG-November_Newsletter_Minnesota_Vikings_partner_for_homegrown_hearing_mission-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:804px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Peterson and Jennings laughed and joked with the children, and each of the players had the opportunity to assist as we fit each patient with brand new top-of-the-line hearing aids, customized to their hearing loss.</p>\n\n<p>Thanks to Starkey Hearing Technologies, the Vikings and these players with generous hearts, each child left with a huge smile and had a day they will never forget.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Happy Thanksgiving!</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_375:{filedir_2}BLOG-November_Newsletter_Minnesota_Vikings_partner_for_homegrown_hearing_mission-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:216px; width:300px\" /></strong></p>\n\n<p>The team just finished giving the gift of hearing during our first visit to Cambodia. We are currently in China changing lives, giving thanks for all of our blessings and the amazing things we experience every day. As you spend time giving thanks with your families and friends, think about the connecting power of hearing.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://action.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/\">Pledge your support</a> today and help us give that same connection to thousands of families in China and the Philippines.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-November_Newsletter_Minnesota_Vikings_partner_for_homegrown_hearing_mission-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(113,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-Dave_Fabry_Lives_to_Listen_Carefully-LEAD.jpg','none','Hearing Missions','none',1383255420,'','none','<p>Dave Fabry, Ph.D. audiologist and Starkey Hearing Technologies&rsquo; Vice President of Audiology and Professional Services, has dedicated his life to hearing care. As a young man in college he was a pre-veterinary medicine major, and his love of animals led him to a hearing lab where scientists were studying the damage from noise exposure in chinchillas. There he found his calling. Since then Fabry has earned a doctorate in audiology from the University of Minnesota, published more than 50 articles and been a leader in the field for more than 30 years. However, he has never let go of his interest in noise exposure and raising awareness on how to prevent hearing loss. He has channeled this passion into our Listen Carefully campaign, and we sat down with him to gain a deeper understanding of the challenges and solutions surrounding preventable hearing loss.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_378:{filedir_2}BLOG-Dave_Fabry_Lives_to_Listen_Carefully-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:944px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>How important is hearing protection?</strong></p>\n\n<p>Hearing protection is critical for all age groups. Look at the history of OSHA and hearing protection in the workplace &ndash; we have done a very good job with occupational noise exposure in the workplace. However, recreational noise exposure has become an increasing problem for both adults and children, which could include anything from concerts to loud restaurants and bars to firearms.</p>\n\n<p>We don&rsquo;t often think of children as being at risk for noise exposure, but in fact, it is a huge concern and an emerging problem in the United States with upwards of 20 percent of teens estimated to suffer from measurable hearing loss. We have to do better at protecting kids from preventable hearing loss.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_379:{filedir_2}BLOG-Dave_Fabry_Lives_to_Listen_Carefully-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:787px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Most of us have been told to wear hearing protection at concerts or to turn down the volume on our headphones to protect our hearing, but what are some of the lesser-known areas where hearing protection should be used?</strong></p>\n\n<p>When looking at dangerous levels of noise exposure, it is all about the intensity of the sound and the duration of exposure. Any sound that is in excess of 85 dB, with extended exposure, will harm your hearing.</p>\n\n<p>There are some really strange places that we don&rsquo;t often think of where dangerous levels of noise exposure can occur. Dentists, for example, are at high risk for noise exposure, due to the sound of the high-frequency drills they use daily. Likewise, the barista at your local coffee shop is at risk for noise exposure due to the sound of the grinder and the high-frequency sound of many cappuccino machines.</p>\n\n<p>In terms of teenagers, one of the places we don&rsquo;t often think of is the school band. The students playing in those bands could be at risk for noise exposure, particularly percussionists and piccolo players and those positioned near them. Violinists are also at a high risk for hearing loss because as they play they place their ears directly against the instrument.</p>\n\n<p>It is important for all of us to take active measures to protect against preventable hearing loss. In my own life I use noise-cancelling headphones on airplanes when I travel to protect against the sounds produced during take off and landing. I also use musicians earplugs when I go to concerts to reduce the sound across the entire frequency spectrum without impacting the sound of the music. I wear those same earplugs when I ride my motorcycle so I can adequately hear other motorists around me while also protecting my hearing. In addition, whenever I mow the grass, I wear hearing protection.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_380:{filedir_2}BLOG-Dave_Fabry_Lives_to_Listen_Carefully-03.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>What are the key issues surrounding noise exposure and iPods and MP3 players?</strong></p>\n\n<p>A popular test of the volume of an iPod or MP3 player is that you should never allow the volume to go over half or two-thirds the maximum. Unfortunately, this is an oversimplification because with today&rsquo;s technology it is actually the headphones that determine the output level. I don&rsquo;t want parents and teens to be lulled into a false sense of security by keeping an iPod at or below half the maximum &ndash; that could still be a level that is damaging.</p>\n\n<p>In addition, years ago, we used to recommend that if someone could stand three feet away from you and sing along with the song you are listening to, the music is too loud. But again, due to the level of technology available for headphones, this also no longer applies.</p>\n\n<p>In an ideal world, we could measure on a simulated ear the level that someone listens to an iPod, and then set the limit, but this is not practical for real-world environments. I would encourage parents to listen to the iPod through your child&rsquo;s headphones, and then set the volume at a level that is comfortable for them and not uncomfortably loud. You can also download sound level meter apps that are pretty accurate. You can then hold your child&rsquo;s headphones up to the sound meter app to get an idea of the sound level and set the volume accordingly.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_381:{filedir_2}BLOG-Dave_Fabry_Lives_to_Listen_Carefully-04.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:815px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>How do you encourage your loved ones to protect their hearing?</strong></p>\n\n<p>I am very particular with the level my daughter listens to music both in the car and on headphones. I always carry hearing protection with me when I go to concerts, so either my wife or my daughter will be encouraged to wear it when they are with me. I have always tried to stress the importance of protecting their hearing against recreational noise exposure.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-Dave_Fabry_Lives_to_Listen_Carefully-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(114,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-October_Newsletter_A_Knight_and_a_Prince_Help_Kick_Off_Fall_Missions-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','News','none',1382653500,'','none','<p><strong>A Knight and a Prince Help Kick Off Fall Missions</strong></p>\n\n<p>Striving for a strong finish to a record-breaking year, the mission team began its fall by spending October giving the gift of hearing in <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/africa/south-africa-10-2013/\">South Africa, Lesotho </a>and Kenya.</p>\n\n<p>The team started out in South Africa where partnered with Sir Richard Branson and <a href=\"http://www.virgin.com/unite\">Virgin Unite </a>for the third time to bring the gift of hearing to hundreds of people in need at Virgin Unite&rsquo;s Bhubezi Healthcare Clinic.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_384:{filedir_2}BLOG-October_Newsletter_A_Knight_and_a_Prince_Help_Kick_Off_Fall_Missions-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:784px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Next, we headed to Lesotho. It was our first hearing mission in the country where we had another wonderful partner in <a href=\"http://sentebale.org/\">Sentebale</a>, a nonprofit organization co-founded by Prince Harry and Prince Seeiso of Lesotho, who participated in the fittings. Patients, ranging from 4 to 101 years old, traveled from all parts of the small, landlocked country to have their hearing assessed and be fitted for hearing aids. For many it was an opportunity to hear for the very first time.</p>\n\n<p>After being honored at the 13th Annual Starkey Hearing Foundation&rsquo;s So the World May Hear Awards Gala in July, Branson joined us to bring the gift of hearing to Virgin Unite&rsquo;s Bhubezi Healthcare Clinic. More than 300 patients from the surrounding Bushbruckridge community were fit with hearing aids. Branson and the Virgin Unite team worked closely with us to ensure each patient left the mission with a new connection to sound and life.</p>\n\n<p>Discussing his continued dedication to the work of the Foundation, Branson said, &ldquo;I admire the Starkey Hearing Foundation for its tireless effort to transform lives with the gift of hearing. I hope it will inspire others, businesses and nonprofits alike, to seek new, innovative and entrepreneurial ways of making a difference in people&rsquo;s lives.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Once the team wrapped up a successful mission in South Africa, we headed to our first mission in Lesotho with new partner Sentebale.</p>\n\n<p>Prince Seeiso joined the team to help fit hearing aids and open up the world of sound to many living in silence and isolation. &ldquo;I have seen children wanting to talk to each other, and their eyes tell a thousand stories,&rdquo; Prince Seeiso said. &ldquo;On behalf of myself, Prince Harry and Sentebale, a big thanks goes to Starkey Hearing Foundation.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>The team is currently in Kenya, where we have traveled from Mombasa to Eldoret to one of the largest slums in Africa, Kibera, to Meru, all the while reflecting caring and connecting communities with the gift of hearing.</p>\n\n<p><strong>2013 Gala Highlights</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_385:{filedir_2}BLOG-October_Newsletter_A_Knight_and_a_Prince_Help_Kick_Off_Fall_Missions-03.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:939px\" /></strong></p>\n\n<p>Whether it was the bald eagle soaring over the crowd as Nita Whitaker sang &ldquo;AmazingGrace,&rdquo; impassioned speeches from twin brothers Ashton and Michael Kutcher, or special surprise guests for Bill Austin, the 2013 So the World May Hear Awards Gala was an evening we will never forget. Our latest film brings you all the highlights and magic from this year&rsquo;s Gala.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KD8h8zNpd48&amp;feature=youtu.be\">Watch as the world comes together to celebrate the power of caring.</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Listen Carefully with Tony Hawk and the Minnesota Vikings</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_386:{filedir_2}BLOG-October_Newsletter_A_Knight_and_a_Prince_Help_Kick_Off_Fall_Missions-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></strong></p>\n\n<p>October is National Protect Your Hearing Month, and we&rsquo;ve been encouraging people toturn down the volume and Listen Carefully with Chris and Kyle Massey at skateboarding legend Tony Hawk&rsquo;s 2013 <a href=\"http://standupforskateparks.org/\">Stand Up for Skateparks </a>and with the help of the Minnesota Vikings.</p>\n\n<p>Remember: Your hearing is fragile. So don&rsquo;t listen loudly. Listen Carefully.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_387:{filedir_2}BLOG-October_Newsletter_A_Knight_and_a_Prince_Help_Kick_Off_Fall_Missions-04.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Chris and Kyle Massey joined our team as we spread the word about the importance of protecting your hearing at the 2013 Stand Up for Skateparks, and we were encouraged to see the message stick as much of the audience wore the hearing protection we distributed during a headlining performance by Modest Mouse.</p>\n\n<p>The Minnesota Vikings have teamed up with our Listen Carefully campaign to encourage fans to protect their hearing, and they are donating $500 to the Foundation for every touchdown scored this season by Adrian Peterson or Greg Jennings. Vikings fans should also be on the look out for Listen Carefully hearing protection at all home games.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Commit Today</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://action.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/\">Pledge your support</a> today and help us change lives during our upcoming missions in Minnesota, India, Cambodia, China and the Philippines.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-October_Newsletter_A_Knight_and_a_Prince_Help_Kick_Off_Fall_Missions-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(115,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-Building_Momentum_for_Peace_in_the_West_Bank-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Hearing Missions','none',1381962840,'','none','<p>Starkey Hearing Foundation is excited to be heading back to the West Bank soon for an upcoming hearing mission. Our work in the region has shown us how hearing brings people together and serves as a vehicle for peace and understanding. Here&#39;s an excited young girl having her ear health evalutated by one of our local partners in preparation for her upcoming hearing aid fitting.</p>\n\n<p>We wanted to share some feedback from a recent mission as we currently prepare for the next one.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Before the mission &ndash; my first &ndash; I was so excited and really didn&rsquo;t know what to expect. Now I can definitely say it was not like anything I had done before. I have lived in this conflict all my life, and today, for the first time I met my neighbors who greeted me with nothing but love. I was amazed to see all the happy faces and know that my small efforts could give someone so much joy. I hope that this mission will take us one step closer to peace, and I hope it won&rsquo;t be the last.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>- Chen Cohen</p>\n\n<p>Our local partners have been hard at work, completing phase one by identifying patients and taking impressions. We look forward to contributing to peace building by continuing to foster connections between people and across cultures through the gift of hearing. Check out the photos below to see the preparation.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_391:{filedir_2}BLOG-Building_Momentum_for_Peace_in_the_West_Bank-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Young boy in the West Bank having impressions taken of his ears that will be turned into custom earmolds for the hearing aids that will soon give him the gift of hearing.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-Building_Momentum_for_Peace_in_the_West_Bank-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(116,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-Reawakening_The_Master-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Events','none',1381358580,'','none','<p>Sir Elton John, Willie Nelson, Ray Charles and countless other music legends call him &ldquo;The Master.&rdquo; His music has been covered and paid homage to by everyone from Joe Cocker, Aretha Franklin and Cher to Michael Buble, Beyonce, Amy Winehouse and Bon Iver. His mastery of piano, musical arrangements and soulful lyrics defy time and musical genre. Leon Russell is the definition of a musician&rsquo;s musician. However, after significant success in the 1960s and 70s, he mysteriously stepped away from the limelight.</p>\n\n<p>While much of the world had forgotten about Russell&rsquo;s immense talent, John never did. In 2009, John decided to remind the world of the brilliance of his mentor and greatest influence by collaborating with Russell on a new album, &ldquo;The Union.&rdquo; Before the two piano men could begin to create what would become No. 3 on Rolling Stone magazine&rsquo;s list of the <a href=\"http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/30-best-albums-of-2010-20101213\">30 Best Albums of 2010</a>, John needed to help Russell address some significant health issues he had been living with, not the least of which was hearing loss.</p>\n\n<p>Russell sufferers from hereditary nerve damage that causes hearing loss. Over the years, he slowly lost his connection to life. He struggled to understand conversations narrating the human interactions that had inspired him to create his music. During a recent visit to Starkey Hearing Foundation, Russell explained where he began to seek inspiration, &ldquo;I haven&rsquo;t been much of a music listener. My hobby is silence.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>A longtime supporter of Starkey Hearing Foundation, John put Russell in touch with Bill Austin as soon as he learned that he was struggling with hearing loss. Once Bill fit him with brand new state-of-the-art hearing aids, Russell went on to write John the song &ldquo;In the Hands of Angels,&rdquo; thanking him for bringing him back from the brink. <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OAkRohrypec&amp;feature=youtu.be\">When John first heard the song</a>, he was overcome with emotion, insisting that the song be a part of their album. With the help of his new hearing aids, Russell was able to perform this song and many others alongside John and continues to perform around the country with his band to this day.</p>\n\n<p>Check out Leon Russell performing &ldquo;In the Hands of Angels&rdquo;:</p>\n\n<p>[gallery id=\"blog-reawakening-the-master-film\"]</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-Reawakening_The_Master-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(117,1,12,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,' ','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(118,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-September_Newsletter_Special_Olympics_Athletes_Recieve_the_Gift_of_Hearing-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Events','none',1380582180,'','none','<p><strong>Special Olympics Athletes Receive the Gift of Hearing</strong></p>\n\n<p>After the team returned from fitting more than 10,000 people in <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/south-america/peru-08-2013/\">Peru </a>and <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/central-america-and-the-caribbean/mexico-09-2013/\">Mexico</a>, our campus was flooded with inspiration when 22 Special Olympics Minnesota athletes and their families arrived for a homegrown mission. The Foundation has partnered with Special Olympics Minnesota on its Healthy Hearing Athletes Initiative, and this mission kicked off what we hope will become a long and life-changing collaboration that will open up the world of sound to all Special Olympics athletes in need. Each athlete was fit with top-of-the-line, customized hearing aids that opened up the world of sound like never before.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_397:{filedir_2}BLOG-September_Newsletter_Special_Olympics_Athletes_Recieve_the_Gift_of_Hearing-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:220px; width:330px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Discussing the significance of this mission, Bill Austin said, &ldquo;We don&rsquo;t believe in disabilities. We believe in ability. Everybody has it, and we have to find it and use it and maximize it.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Former Minnesota Viking Matt Blair was also on hand to support the athletes, including his good friend Katie Timmer. She has been participating in Special Olympics for more than 30 years and met Blair at a golf tournament. Over the years, Blair has become Timmer&rsquo;s biggest fan. Unfortunately, She suffered from a hearing loss that had begun to affect her performance, but once she received the gift of hearing, she couldn&rsquo;t wait to get back out on the golf course.</p>\n\n<p>Special Olympics president, Dave Dorn, said the partnership with the Foundation would make a huge difference in each of the athlete&rsquo;s lives.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a <a href=\"http://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2013/09/17/starkey-steps-up-to-aid-minnesotas-special-olympians/\">confidence </a>builder,&rdquo; Dorn said. &ldquo;They can be engaged in conversations and hear the world around them. All of a sudden they are much more participatory and active in their surroundings because they can hear what&rsquo;s going on.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>The mission team is currently on its way to South Africa which will be followed by missions in Lesotho and Kenya.</p>\n\n<p><strong>The Power of Partnerships</strong></p>\n\n<p>President Bill Clinton and Chelsea Clinton once again joined the team on a recent mission swing through in Zambia, Tanzania and Rwanda to see our 1 million hearing aid commitment in action. Our latest film showcases the power of partnerships in providing the gift of hearing and tackling some of the world&rsquo;s most challenging issues.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TQzsRpCYics\">Watch as powerful organizations come together to create lasting change.</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Join us for a Hearing Protection Twitter Chat!</strong></p>\n\n<p>October is National Protect Your Hearing Month! Research shows that 1 in 5 teens in the United States has hearing loss, largely due to high-volume sounds in daily life, such as music streamed loudly into headphones. Most hearing loss among teens can be avoided if simple protective measures &ndash; such as lowering the volume &ndash; are taken.<img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_398:{filedir_2}BLOG-September_Newsletter_Special_Olympics_Athletes_Recieve_the_Gift_of_Hearing-03.jpg}\" style=\"height:82px; width:330px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Your hearing is fragile. So don&rsquo;t listen loudly. Listen Carefully.</p>\n\n<p>Join us on Twitter Thursday, October 3, from 12-1 p.m. CDT as Starkey Hearing Foundation and Starkey Hearing Technologies discuss ways to protect your hearing and prevent hearing loss!</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re new to Twitter chats, <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/blog/join-us-for-a-hearing-protection-twitter-chat/\">here&rsquo;s an overview of how it works</a>&hellip;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Commit Today</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://action.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=298\">Pledge your support today</a> and help us change a life during our upcoming missions in South Africa or Lesotho.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-September_Newsletter_Special_Olympics_Athletes_Recieve_the_Gift_of_Hearing-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(119,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'true','none','BLOG-Join_us_for_a_Hearing_Protection_Twitter_Chat-THUMBNAIL.png','none','Listen Carefully','none',1380582840,'','none','<p>October is National Protect Your Hearing Month! Research shows that 1 in 5 teens in the United States has hearing loss, largely due to high-volume sounds in daily life, such as music streamed loudly into headphones. Most hearing loss among teens can be avoided if simple protective measures &ndash; such as lowering the volume &ndash; are taken.</p>\n\n<p>Your hearing is fragile. So don&rsquo;t listen loudly. Listen Carefully.</p>\n\n<p>Join us on Twitter Thursday, October 3 from 12-1 p.m. Central time as Starkey Hearing Foundation and Starkey Hearing Technologies discuss ways to protect your hearing and prevent hearing loss!</p>\n\n<p><strong>What&rsquo;s a Twitter chat?</strong><br />\nTwitter chats happen when a group of people all tweet about the same topic using a specific hashtag that allows it to be followed on Twitter.</p>\n\n<p><strong>How to participate:</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. If you don&rsquo;t already have a Twitter account, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/signup\">sign up here</a> and check out this post on <a href=\"https://support.twitter.com/groups/50-welcome-to-twitter/topics/204-the-basics/articles/215585-twitter-101-getting-started-with-twitter#\">Twitter 101</a>!<br />\n2. Be sure to follow the Twitter chat moderators:</p>\n\n<p>Starkey Hearing Foundation: <a href=\"http://twitter.com/starkeycares\">@starkeycares</a><br />\nStarkey Hearing Technologies: <a href=\"https://twitter.com/starkeyhearing\">@starkeyhearing</a></p>\n\n<p>3. To listen and add to the discussion, monitor the hashtag<a href=\"http://twitter.com/search?q=%23hearingchat&amp;src=typd&amp;f=realtime\"> #hearingchat </a>and include the hashtag in your tweets.<br />\nYou can follow the chat in Twitter at the above link, just be sure to select &ldquo;all&rdquo; tweets at the top of the timeline.</p>\n\n<p>There are also free tools available like <a href=\"http://tweetchat.com/\">TweetChat</a> and<a href=\"http://hootsuite.com/\"> HootSuite </a>that help you follow a hashtag, your feed and @mentions simultaneously.</p>\n\n<p>4. Chime in! Once the chat starts, feel free to share thoughts, ask questions and retweet others&rsquo; posts. Don&rsquo;t forget to include the hashtag #hearingchat in all your tweets!</p>\n\n<p>We hope to see you tweeting with us!</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-Join_us_for_a_Hearing_Protection_Twitter_Chat-LEAD.png','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(120,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'false','none','BLOG-One_on_One_With_The_Masseys-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Hearing Missions','none',1378337220,'','none','<p>For years, Chris and Kyle Massey have dedicated themselves to helping deliver the gift of hearing. From Vietnam to Mexico to Tanzania to our most recent mission in Peru, the Massey brothers are always up for an adventure that includes connecting people in need to the sounds of life. We sat down with them in Peru to discuss their long-standing support of the Foundation&rsquo;s work and what it means to their lives.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_403:{filedir_2}BLOG-One_on_One_With_The_Masseys-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:777px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>How many missions have you been on?</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chris</strong>: Nine, including international and domestic missions. We plan on doing as many more as we can for the rest of our lives.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Kyle</strong>: Absolutely!</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_404:{filedir_2}BLOG-One_on_One_With_The_Masseys-04.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:953px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>What do you like about the people of Peru?</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Kyle</strong>: Peru is an amazing place. The people here are so appreciative, and they are always so happy. It brings smiles to our faces to know that they really appreciate what we do. They are so genuine, and it makes it all worthwhile.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Chris</strong>: Every day we share these cool moments with people. We might not ever see any of these people again, but we share these life-changing moments with them. If I ever do see any of them again in my life, we are going to know exactly who each other are because these moments shared through the gift of hearing are unforgettable.</p>\n\n<p>I have had a few people I helped with their hearing aids find me on Twitter. They send me a tweet saying, &ldquo;Thank you for helping me with my hearing aids,&rdquo; and it is really cool to be able to stay connected and hear about their progress.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_405:{filedir_2}DSC06887ccPeru-Day-15-Piura-Aug-26-Mon.jpg}\" style=\"height:673px; width:1024px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>What has been your favorite experience as a hearing mission volunteer in Peru?</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Kyle</strong>: Being able to help a woman who is 108 years old. She is amazing! She heard about this mission and came down here to get her hearing aids. Bill Austin said, &ldquo;Even when you are 108, you don&rsquo;t want to be alone, and you want to be able to hear.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_407:{filedir_2}BLOG-One_on_One_With_The_Masseys-03.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:796px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>What do you guys like about being a part of the Starkey Hearing Foundation?</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chris</strong>: It is like a family, and I love being a part of it.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Kyle</strong>: I think you need trips like this. Especially when you live in the craziness we live in. We live in Hollywood, and we see just the craziest stuff every day &ndash; people&rsquo;s priorities are often not the same as ours. Having the opportunity to know people who do not have much but are happy and smiling because of something as basic as the gift of hearing, it&rsquo;s refreshing. More people need to seek out experiences like this.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_408:{filedir_2}BLOG-One_on_One_With_The_Masseys-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:790px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chris</strong>: We definitely want to get more young people involved in things like this. Some of the patients are older, but many of them are our age or younger. We helped one kid who was going to school for engineering, and he was about my age. He was embarrassed that he had to get a hearing aid, and we made him feel comfortable. He saw that we were here enjoying ourselves and laughing, and he realized that getting a hearing aid was not a big deal, and he shouldn&rsquo;t be embarrassed about. It was just life.</p>\n\n<p>Spreading positivity to others is amazing.</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-One_on_One_With_The_Masseys-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(121,1,20,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',