 aliquyam erat, sed diam voluptua. At vero eos et accusam et justo duo dolores et ea rebum.</p>','none',' ','xhtml',' ','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(124,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'false','none','BLOG-August_Newsletter_President_Bill_Clinton_Continues_Support_for_Global_Fight_Against_Hearing_Loss-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Hearing Missions','none',1377887940,'','none','<p><strong>President Clinton Continues Support for Global Fight Against Hearing Loss</strong></p>\n\n<p>During a ten-day Africa trip with the Clinton Foundation, former President Bill Clinton and Chelsea Clinton joined the mission team to fit more than 375 people in Livingstone, Zambia and Kigali, Rwanda with hearing aids. They made the stops to see the progress the Foundation is making on its Clinton Global Initiative Commitment to Action of providing 1 million hearing aids to people in need this decade. Currently, we are nearly 40 percent ahead of schedule, fitting more than 165,000 hearing aids worldwide in the last year alone.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_421:{filedir_2}BLOG-August_Newsletter_President_Bill_Clinton_Continues_Support_for_Global_Fight_Against_Hearing_Loss-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:223px; width:330px\" /></p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Starkey Hearing Foundation is empowering people around the world to achieve a better life through the gift of hearing,&rdquo; said President Clinton. &ldquo;Chelsea and I were honored, as we always are, to help the great Starkey staff fit people, many of whom had never heard before, for hearing aids.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>President Clinton and Chelsea Clinton personally fitted patients with new hearing aids in both Zambia and Rwanda. President Clinton has spoken at Starkey&rsquo;s annual So the World May Hear Awards Gala for the last four years, including most recently on July 28, in St. Paul, Minn. This was his third time volunteering on a mission. He joined the Foundation in Colombia and Uganda in 2012.</p>\n\n<p>Discussing the former president&rsquo;s dedication to the global fight against hearing loss, Bill Austin said, &ldquo;The support we received from President Clinton and the Clinton Global Initiative has enabled us to build vital partnerships and touch more lives than we ever thought possible.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Mission partners Global Health Corps and Bridge2Rwanda also worked with the team in Rwanda. Actors Jesse Eisenberg and Dakota Fanning joined us in Zambia. In between missions in Zambia and Rwanda, the mission team made an additional stop in <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/africa/tanzania-07-2013/\">Tanzania</a>, along with Tanzanian-born Hasheem Thabeet, of the NBA&rsquo;s Oklahoma City Thunder, to give the gift of hearing to more than 200 people in need.</p>\n\n<p>The mission team is currently delivering the gift of hearing to nearly 10,000 patients in Peru.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Building Sustainable Systems of Hearing Care</strong></p>\n\n<p>To truly make an impact, our efforts must be sustainable. Our recent short film highlights our efforts in Rwanda and shows how, by working closely with on-the-ground partners, we bring patients long-term hearing care. The Rwanda program exemplifies how we incorporate a full-circle approach that ensures patients will be connected to the world of sound for years to come.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_422:{filedir_2}BLOG-August_Newsletter_President_Bill_Clinton_Continues_Support_for_Global_Fight_Against_Hearing_Loss-03.jpg}\" style=\"height:185px; width:330px\" /></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W50L7eNGT2U\">Watch our efforts to build sustainable systems of hearing care.</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Commit Today</strong></p>\n\n<p>Thanks to your support,<a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/galas/\"> the 2013 So the World May Hear Awards Gala</a> set a new record! People from all over the world came together to make this year&rsquo;s event one of our best, but if you were not able to attend, you can still be a part of the spirit of caring that inspired so many.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://action.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/\">Donate today</a>, and you will help us provide nearly 20,000 hearing aids to the people of Peru!</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_423:{filedir_2}BLOG-August_Newsletter_President_Bill_Clinton_Continues_Support_for_Global_Fight_Against_Hearing_Loss-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:216px; width:330px\" /></p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-August_Newsletter_President_Bill_Clinton_Continues_Support_for_Global_Fight_Against_Hearing_Loss-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(125,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'false','none','BLOG-July_Newsletter_President_George_W_Bush_Joins_Us_in_Tanzania-THUMBNAIL.jpg','none','Hearing Missions','none',1374778800,'','none','<p><strong>President George W. Bush Joins Us in Tanzania</strong></p>\n\n<p>Starkey Hearing Foundation&rsquo;s weeklong mission in Tanzania started off with a bang! President George W. Bush personally joined the mission team in Dar es Salaam to help change the lives of people in need.</p>\n\n<p>Donning one of the Foundation&rsquo;s blue polo shirts and a mission tool belt, President Bush took the time to shake hands with the volunteers before getting down to the business of fitting hearing aids. The former president was completely engaged&mdash;wanting to experience every step of the process, and after some training from Bill Austin, he put his glasses on and dove right into giving the gift of hearing.</p>\n\n<p>President Bush was very involved in fitting a brother and sister. Once Austin explained to him the importance of vocalization for child development, particularly for children with new hearing aids, President Bush began to encourage the siblings to use their voices. As soon as the children started repeating sounds, the president hugged the parents and celebrated with them. We were honored to experience such hands-on support from the former president.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Hearing is a powerful gift that brings people together, opens doors and gives individuals the power to seize opportunities and reach their full potential in life,&rdquo; said Austin. &ldquo;President Bush has done amazing things across Africa in HIV/AIDS and cancer prevention and treatment, and we are incredibly grateful that he supports us in our fight for better hearing.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>After completing missions in <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/africa/tanzania-07-2013/\">Tanzania </a>and <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/missions/africa/malawi-07-2013/\">Malawi</a>, the mission team is back in Minneapolis for the So the World May Hear <a href=\"http://www.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/galas/\">Awards Gala</a>, before heading to Peru in August.</p>\n\n<p><strong>The power of partnership</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_426:{filedir_2}BLOG-July_Newsletter_President_George_W_Bush_Joins_Us_in_Tanzania-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:194px; width:320px\" /></strong></p>\n\n<p>The rural and expansive nature of Honduras creates challenges when reaching out to those in need of hearing care. Fortunately, skilled and powerful partners, like Operation Honduras and Starkey Canada, make those challenges much less formidable. Our latest short film highlights the incredible work of our long-term, on-the-ground partners and mission volunteers who dedicate themselves to finding people who need to hear.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z8qsLNhDuRQ\">Watch our efforts to build sustainable systems of hearing care.</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Watch the stars align &mdash; Join the conversation on July 28</strong></p>\n\n<p>The 2013 So the World May Hear Awards Gala is upon us! On Sunday, people from all over the world will come together in St. Paul, Minnesota to celebrate the spirit of giving.</p>\n\n<p>Even if you aren&rsquo;t in attendance, you too can be a part of this incredible evening! Join in the Gala buzz on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/StarkeyCares\">Facebook</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/starkeycares\">Twitter </a>and <a href=\"http://instagram.com/starkeycares#\">Instagram</a>. Check out and use these hashtags:</p>\n\n<p>#starkeygala<br />\n#operationchange</p>\n\n<p>See what all the fuss is about, and join us in celebrating the tremendous impact of reflecting caring and sharing into the lives of others.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_427:{filedir_2}BLOG-July_Newsletter_President_George_W_Bush_Joins_Us_in_Tanzania-02.jpg}\" style=\"height:263px; width:300px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Commit Today</strong></p>\n\n<p>The gift of hearing inspires great things, but it comes at a price. We need your help! &ldquo;Alone we can&rsquo;t do much. Together we can change the world.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://action.starkeyhearingfoundation.org/\">Pledge your support </a>today and help us fit more than 20,000 hearing aids next month in Peru!</p>','none','Foundation Staff ','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','xhtml','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'BLOG-July_Newsletter_President_George_W_Bush_Joins_Us_in_Tanzania-LEAD.jpg','none','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','none','','xhtml','','none','','xhtml','','xhtml'),(126,1,5,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'false','none','BLOG-Bringing_Peace_Through_Hearing-West_Bank-THUMBNAIL.png','none','News','none',1301608080,'','none','<p>A historic mission for the Starkey Hearing Foundation, we went on the ultimate peace and understanding through Hearing Mission with Sheba Medical Center at Tel Hashomer,Physicians for Human Rights- Israel and American Friends of SHeba Medical Center in New York. The Starkey team landed on the 23rd of May ready to work.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_429:{filedir_2}BLOG-Bringing_Peace_Through_Hearing-West_Bank-01.jpg}\" style=\"height:525px; width:703px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Crossing the border into the West Bank, they call it the Green Line, was a little intimidating. There was no record of us coming, but the Head of &nbsp;Sheba Medical said we are going in anyway, so we finally made it in. Once in the town of Tulkarm, there were hundreds of patients already waiting for us. We went to work.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_430:{filedir_2}BLOG-Bringing_Peace_Through_Hearing-West_Bank-02.jpg}\" /></p>\n\n<p>We have worked in Turkey, Egypt and Zanzibar all of which are Arabic influenced, so the core Starkey team was used to the culture of the Arabic ways, aggressive but also expressive&nbsp;and warm and always hugging and kissing!</p>\n\n<p>The electricity in the front compound of the school was extreme. Israeli Jews working with and touching Palestinians! They could not even believe this was happening. Starkey Hearing Foundation brought shirts for everyone so we could be one team. It worked, you couldn&rsquo;t tell the Israeli&rsquo;s from the Palestinians from the Americans! We all looked the same and worked side-by-side bringing peace and understanding through hearing.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_431:{filedir_2}BLOG-Bringing_Peace_Through_Hearing-West_Bank-03.png}\" style=\"height:525px; width:393px\" /></p>\n\n<p>It is very important to the Palestinians that the Starkey Hearing Foundation stops and eat lunch, so we all sat, SHF, Israeli&rsquo;s, Palestinians, and Palestinian Military all sitting on elementary chairs eating lunch in this small classroom TOGETHER!!! It was something I cannot even describe, intense, polite, friendly and strange, I felt like it was a movie scene&hellip; Incredible!</p>\n\n<p>Lots of better hearing smiles on all faces. Salah Hay Yihveh ,Physicians of Human Rights , said we made his heart open! That statement right there made my day. He was in charge of the project on the Palestinian side and did an extraordinary job on logistics.</p>\n\n<p>It has been a moving experience, one that I will never forget.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"{assets_432:{filedir_2}BLOG-Bringing_Peace_Through_Hearing-West_Bank-04.png}\" style=\"height:525px; width:838px\" /></p>'